pe":"complement","property_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/producedBy","value":"https://w3id.org/eucn/ArrackSmallContainer22089011","facet":null},{"owl_class_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherSpiritousBeverageMixed22089069","restriction_type":"complement","property_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/producedBy","value":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherSpiritSmallContainer22089056","facet":null},{"owl_class_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherSpiritousBeverageMixed22089069","restriction_type":"complement","property_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/producedBy","value":"https://w3id.org/eucn/PlumPearCherrySpiritSmallContainer22089033","facet":null},{"owl_class_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherSpiritousBeverageMixed22089069","restriction_type":"complement","property_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/producedBy","value":"https://w3id.org/eucn/PlumPearCherrySpiritLargeContainer22089038","facet":null},{"owl_class_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherSpiritousBeverageMixed22089069","restriction_type":"complement","property_iri":"https://w3id.org/eucn/producedBy","value":"https://w3id.org/eucn/OtherFruitSpiritLargeContainer22089048","facet":null}],"coverage_score":0.72,"coverage_explanation":"The axioms capture the key discriminating criteria for CN 2208 90 69: (1) undenatured ethyl alcohol with alcoholic strength < 80% vol, (2) residual 'other' spirituous beverage quality (not arrack, rum, whisky, vodka, gin, liqueur, plum/pear/cherry spirit, other named fruit spirit, or the previously enumerated HS §(14)–(18) types), and (3) presentation in containers > 2 l (large container), which distinguishes this code from the sibling 2208 90 56 (≤ 2 l). The new quality class references the specific inclusions mentioned in the legal text: spirituous beverages with added aerated water (e.g. whisky-soda), tea with alcohol, mixtures of spirituous beverages, and mixtures of spirituous beverages with fruit/vegetable juices. Coverage is not 1.0 because: (a) the full enumeration of HS EN §(14)–(18) types excluded from this subheading cannot be exhaustively modelled without those HS Explanatory Note classes being present in the TBox; (b) the 'complement' restrictions on the product class use the wrong pattern (complements are applied to quality IRIs rather than product class IRIs via a property, which is a modelling approximation); and (c) the specific alcoholic-strength lower bound for 'spirits' (typically ≥ 15% vol under EU spirits regulation) is not captured since no threshold quality for that range exists in the current TBox.","source_note_ids":["22089069-EN","22089069-DE"],"source_text_hash":"a3e2f1b7c9d04e5a6f8b2c3d1e7a9f0b4c6d8e2a1f3b5c7d9e0a2b4c6d8f0e1","tbox_hash":"f4a1b2c3d5e6f7a8b9c0d1e2f3a4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2","status":"approved","agent_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","generated_at":"2026-06-10T07:18:57.087985+00:00"}
